A Sri Lankan soldier checks the body temperature of a woman in Colombo, Sri Lanka on Thursday, after a three-day curfew was announced from Friday to contain the spread of the coronavirus. Sri Lanka's Army Commander Lt. Gen. Shavendra Silva said the first contacts of COVID-19 patients would undergo home quarantine from Tuesday and would not be taken to quarantine centers, as the number of patients saw a spike in recent weeks. Photo: AFP 
